{"parse":{"title":"fungus","pageid":38448,"redirects":[],"wikitext":"==English==\n{{wp}}\n\n===Etymology===\nBorrowed from {{bor|en|la|fungus||mushroom}}.\n\n{{picdic\n|image=AD2009Sep13 Boletus edulis 01.jpg\n|detail1=\n{{picdicimg|en|image=Eukaryota diversity 2.jpg|link=organism}}\n|detail2=\n{{picdicimg|en|image=Brot-Schimmel.JPG|link=mold|anchor=#Etymology_2}}\n{{picdicimg|en|image=Flammulina velutipes 04.jpg|link=mushroom}}\n}}\n\n===Pronunciation===\n* {{IPA|en|/ˈfʌŋ.ɡəs/|a=RP,US}}\n** {{audio|en|en-us-fungus.ogg|a=US}}\n* {{IPA|en|/fʊŋ.ɡəs/|a=Northern England,Midlands}}\n* {{rhymes|en|ʌŋɡəs|s=2}}\n\n===Noun===\n{{en-noun|~|fungi|+<l:uncommon>|fungusses<l:nonstandard,rare>|*}}\n\n# {{senseid|en|Q764}} {{lb|en|mycology}} A [[eukaryotic]] [[organism]] of the kingdom {{taxfmt|Fungi|kingdom}} typically having [[chitin]] [[cell wall]]s but no [[chlorophyll]] or [[plastid]]s. Fungi may be unicellular or multicellular.\n#: {{hyper|en|organism<id:Q7239>}}\n#: {{hypo|en|ascomycete<id:Q174726>|basidiomycete<id:Q174698>|mold<id:Q159341>|mushroom<id:fungus that produces Q83093>|yeast<id:Q45422>}}\n#* {{quote-journal|en|date=2013-07-20|volume=408|issue=8845|magazine=w:The Economist\n|titleurl=http://www.economist.com/news/science-and-technology/21581981-what-pollution-some-opportunity-others-welcome-plastisphere|title=Welcome to the plastisphere\n|passage=Plastics are energy-rich substances, which is why many of them burn so readily. Any organism that could unlock and use that energy would do well in the Anthropocene. Terrestrial bacteria and '''fungi''' which can manage this trick are already familiar to experts in the field.|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20200814005537/https://www.economist.com/science-and-technology/2013/07/20/welcome-to-the-plastisphere}}\n# {{lb|en|uncountable}} The [[flesh]] of [[#English:_Q764|such an organism]].\n# {{lb|en|archaic|pathology}} A [[spongy]], [[abnormal]] [[excrescence]], such as excessive [[granulation tissue]] formed in a [[wound]].\n\n====Derived terms====\n{{col|en\n|{{vern|coal fungus}} ({{taxlink|Daldinia concentrica|species}})\n|ambrosia fungus\n|fungus gamboge\n|orange-peel fungus\n|antifungus\n|tinder fungus\n|artillery fungus\n|artist's fungus\n|bird's nest fungus\n|black fungus\n|bleeding tooth fungus| candlestick fungus|distillery fungus|whisky fungus\n|bracket fungus\n|cannonball fungus\n|caterpillar fungus\n|cinnamon fungus|fairy ring fungus\n|clavarioid fungus\n|club fungus\n|coral fungus\n|cup fungus\n|dark fungus\n|endofungus|bootlace fungus|cauliflower fungus|white fungus\n|face fungus\n|fly fungus\n|fungal\n|fungicidal\n|fungicide\n|fungoid\n|fungology|smut fungus\n|fungus beetle\n|fungus comb\n|fungused\n|fungus garden\n|fungus gnat\n|fungus-growing ant\n|funguslike\n|fungus moth\n|fungusproof\n|fungus weevil\n|fungusy\n|ghost fungus\n|golden jelly fungus\n|honey fungus\n|hoof fungus\n|jelly fungus\n|macrofungus\n|microfungus\n|nail fungus\n|panfungus\n|phytofungus\n|pleasing fungus beetle\n|pseudofungus\n|rust fungus\n|sac fungus\n|sewage fungus\n|shelf fungus\n|shotgun fungus\n|smellfungus\n|snow fungus\n|sulfur fungus\n|sulphur fungus\n|toothed jelly fungus\n|tooth fungus\n|whiskey fungus\n|yellow brain fungus\n|zombie fungus\n}}\n\n====Related terms====\n* {{l|en|fungous|pos=adj}}\n\n====Descendants====\n* {{desc|ga|fungas|bor=1}}\n\n====Translations====\n{{trans-top|any member of the kingdom ''Fungi''}}\n* Afrikaans: {{t|af|swam}}, {{t|af|fungus}}\n* Albanian: {{t|sq|këpurdhë|f}}\n* Arabic: {{t+|ar|فُطْر|m}}\n*: Egyptian Arabic: {{t|arz|فطر|m|tr=feṭr}}\n* Armenian: {{t+|hy|սունկ}}, {{t+|hy|սնկիկ}}, {{t+|hy|բորբոս}}\n* Assamese: {{t|as|ভেঁকুৰ}}\n* Asturian: {{t|ast|fungu|m}}\n* Azerbaijani: {{t+|az|göbələk}}\n* Bashkir: {{t|ba|бәшмәктәр}}\n* Belarusian: {{t|be|грыбо́к|m}}\n* Bengali: {{t+|bn|ছত্রাক}}\n* Breton: {{t+|br|foue}}\n* Bulgarian: {{t+|bg|гъба|f}}\n* Burmese: {{t+|my|မှို}}\n* Catalan: {{t+|ca|fong}}\n* Chinese:\n*: Hokkien: {{t|nan-hbl|ko͘}}\n*: Mandarin: {{t+|cmn|菌類|tr=jūnlèi}}, {{t+|cmn|真菌|tr=zhēnjūn}}\n* Chuvash: {{t|cv|кӑмпа}}\n* Czech: {{t+|cs|houba|f}}\n* Danish: {{t+|da|svamp|c}}\n* Dutch: {{t+|nl|zwam|m}}\n* Erzya: {{t|myv|пангт}}\n* Esperanto: {{t+|eo|fungo}}\n* Estonian: {{t+|et|seen}}\n* Faroese: {{t|fo|soppur}}\n* Finnish: {{t+|fi|sieni}}\n* French: {{t+|fr|fongus|m}}\n* Galician: {{t+|gl|fungo|m}}\n* Georgian: {{t|ka|სოკო}}\n* German: {{t+|de|Pilz|m}}\n*: Alemannic German: {{t|gsw|Pilz|m}}\n* Greek: {{t+|el|μύκητας|m}}\n* Hawaiian: {{t|haw|kalina}}\n* Hebrew: {{t+|he|פטרייה|f|tr=pitriyá}}\n* Hindi: {{t|hi|फफूंद|f}}, {{t+|hi|फफूँद|f}}\n* Hungarian: {{t+|hu|gombaféle}}, {{t+|hu|gomba}}\n* Iban: {{t|iba|kulat}}\n* Icelandic: {{t+|is|sveppur}}\n* Irish: {{t|ga|fungas|m}}\n* Italian: {{t+|it|fungo}}\n* Japanese: {{t+|ja|菌類|tr=きんるい, kinrui}}, {{t+|ja|真菌|tr=しんきん, shinkin}}, {{t+|ja|茸|tr=きのこ, kinoko}}\n* Kannada: {{t+|kn|ಶಿಲೀಂಧ್ರ}}\n* Khmer: {{t+|km|ផ្សិត}}\n* Kongo:  {{t-needed|kg}}\n* Korean: {{t|ko|균계}}\n* Lao: {{t|lo|ເຫັດ}}\n* Latin: {{t|la|fungus}}\n* Latvian: {{t+|lv|sēnes}}\n* Lingala: {{t|ln|liyɛbú}}\n* Lithuanian: {{t+|lt|grybas}}\n* Low German: {{t|nds|Swamm|m}}\n* Luxembourgish: {{t|lb|Pilzeräich}}\n* Macedonian: {{t|mk|габа|f}}\n* Malay: {{t+|ms|kulat}}\n*: Brunei Malay: {{t|kxd|kulat}}\n* Manx: {{t|gv|fungys|m}}\n* Māori: {{t|mi|kōpurawhetū}}, {{t|mi|hekaheka}}, {{t|mi|puruheka}}\n* Marathi: {{t|mr|बुरशी|f}}\n* Melanau:\n*: Central Melanau: {{t|mel|kulat}}\n* Nahuatl: {{t+|nah|nanacatl}}\n* Norwegian: {{t+|no|sopp}}\n* Occitan: {{t+|oc|fonge}}\n* Persian: {{t+|fa|قارچ|tr=qârč}}\n* Plautdietsch: {{t|pdt|Pilz|n}}\n* Polish: {{t+|pl|grzyb|m}}\n* Portuguese: {{t+|pt|fungo|m}}\n* Quechua: {{t+|qu|k'allampa}}\n* Romanian: {{t+|ro|ciupercă|f}}\n* Russian: {{t+|ru|гриб|m}}, {{t+|ru|грибо́к|m}}\n* Sami:\n*: Northern Sami: {{t|se|guobbarat}}\n* Samogitian: {{t|sgs|kremblē}}\n* Sanskrit: {{t+|sa|कवकम्}}\n* Sardinian: {{t|sc|cordolinu}}\n* Scottish Gaelic: {{t|gd|fungas|m}}\n* Serbo-Croatian: {{t+|sh|gljȉva|f}}, {{t|sh|гљива|f}}\n* Slovak: {{t+|sk|huba|f}}\n* Spanish: {{t+|es|hongo|m}}\n* Sranan Tongo: {{t|srn|buku}}\n* Swahili: {{t+|sw|kuvu}}\n* Swedish: {{t+|sv|svamp}}\n* Tagalog: {{t|tl|halamang-singaw}}, {{t|tl|buot}}, {{t|tl|apugaw}}, {{t|tl|kolatkolat}}\n* Tajik: {{t|tg|занбӯруғ}}\n* Tamil: {{t|ta|பூஞ்சைகள்}}\n* Telugu: {{t+|te|శిలీంధ్రం}}\n* Thai: {{t|th|เห็ดรา|tr=hèt-raa}}\n* Tongan: {{t|to|talingelinga}}\n* Turkish: {{t+|tr|mantar}}\n*: Ottoman Turkish: {{t|ota|مانطار|tr=mantar}}\n* Ukrainian: {{t+|uk|гриб|m}}, {{t|uk|грибо́к}} {{qualifier|microscopic, non formal}}\n* Uzbek: {{t+|uz|zamburugʻ}}\n* Vietnamese: {{t+|vi|nấm}}\n* Volapük: {{t+|vo|funig}}\n* Walloon: {{t+|wa|tchampion}}\n* Welsh: {{t+|cy|ffwng|m}}\n* Xhosa: {{t|xh|ikhowa}}, {{t|xh|inkowane}}\n* Yiddish: {{t|yi|פֿונגוס|m}}, {{t|yi|שוואָם|m|f}}\n{{trans-bottom}}\n\n==Dutch==\n\n===Etymology===\nBorrowed from {{bor|nl|la|fungus}}.\n\n===Pronunciation===\n* {{IPA|nl|/ˈfʏŋ.ɡʏs/|/ˈfʏŋ.ɣʏs/}}\n* {{audio|nl|Nl-fungus.ogg}}\n* {{hyphenation|nl|fun|gus}}\n\n===Noun===\n{{nl-noun|m|fungi|-}}\n\n# {{lb|nl|mycology}} {{l|en|fungus}}, member of the kingdom {{taxfmt|Fungi|kingdom}}\n\n====Related terms====\n* {{l|nl|fungicidaal}}\n* {{l|nl|fungicide}}\n* {{l|nl|spons}}\n\n==French==\n\n===Pronunciation===\n* {{fr-IPA|fongusse}}\n\n===Noun===\n{{fr-noun|m}}\n\n# {{alternative spelling of|fr|fongus}}\n\n==Indonesian==\n\n===Etymology===\nFrom {{der|id|la|fungus}}.\n\n===Pronunciation===\n{{id-pr}}\n\n===Noun===\n{{head|id|noun}}\n\n# {{l|en|fungus}} {{gl|any member of the kingdom {{taxfmt|Fungi|kingdom}}}}\n\n====Related terms====\n{{col|id\n|fungi\n}}\n\n{{C|id|Mycology}}\n\n==Latin==\n[[Image:Morchella conica 1 beentree.jpg|thumb|fungus (a mushroom)]]\n\n===Etymology===\n{{etymon|la|<alt:*sfungus>}}\nOriginally {{m|la||*sfungus}}. Along with {{cog|grc|σπόγγος||sponge|ng=whence Latin {{m|la|spongia}}}}, {{m|grc|σφόγγος}}, and {{cog|xcl|սունկն}}, likely a loanword from a non-Indo-European {{bor|la|qfa-sub}} language. Possibly also related to {{cog|ka|სოკო}}, {{cog|ddo|зикӀу}}, {{cog|kap|сакӀо}}, {{cog|mdf|панга}} and {{cog|myv|панго||mushroom}}. Linguists such as Kluge and Kroonen have suggested a connection to {{cog|en|swamp}} and its Germanic cognates.\n\n===Pronunciation===\n* {{la-IPA}}\n\n===Noun===\n{{la-noun|fungus<2>}}\n\n# [[mushroom]]; {{l|en|fungus}}\n# [[fungal]] [[growth]] or [[infection]]\n# [[candle]]-[[snuff]]\n# {{lb|la|figuratively|derogatory}} [[dolt]], [[idiot]]\n#: {{syn|la|Thesaurus:homo stultus}}\n\n====Declension====\n{{la-ndecl|fungus<2>}}\n\n====Derived terms====\n* {{l|la|fungifōrmis}}\n* {{l|la|fungīnus}}\n* {{l|la|fungōsus}}\n* {{l|la|fungulus}}\n\n====Related terms====\n* {{l|la|fungidus}}\n\n====Descendants====\n{{top2}}\n* Italo-Dalmatian:\n** {{desc|it|fungo}}\n** {{desc|nap|fungio}}\n** {{desc|scn|funcia|funciu}}\n** {{desc|vec|fongo|fonc}}\n* Rhaeto-Romance:\n** {{desc|fur|fonc|fong}}\n* Gallo-Italic:\n** {{desc|egl|fónnż|fonz|fons}}\n** {{desc|lij|fonzo}}\n** {{desc|lmo|fons|fonz|foncc|fonze}}\n** {{desc|pms|fons}}\n** {{desc|rgn|fons|fong}}\n* Gallo-Romance:\n** {{desc|ca|fong|unc=1|qq=perhaps a borrowing from Aragonese/Spanish}}\n* Ibero-Romance:\n** {{desc|an|fongo|frongo}}\n** {{desctree|osp|fongo}}\n* Borrowings:\n** {{desc|ast|fungu|bor=1}}\n** {{desc|eu|onddo|bor=1}}\n** {{desc|nl|fungus|bor=1}}\n*** {{desc|id|fungus|bor=1}}\n** {{desc|en|fungus|bor=1}}\n** {{desc|fr|fonge|fongus|fungus|bor=1}}\n** {{desc|ga|fungas|bor=1}}\n** {{desc|gl|fungo|bor=1}}\n** {{desc|pt|fungo|bor=1}}\n** {{desc|ro|fungă|bor=1}}\n{{bottom}}\n\n===References===\n* {{R:itc:EDL}}\n* {{R:xcl:Martirosyan|pages=586–587}}\n* {{R:la:L&S}}\n* {{R:la:Elementary Lewis}}\n* {{R:la:du Cange}}\n* {{R:la:Gaffiot}}\n* {{R:la:M&A}}\n\n{{C|la|Mushrooms}}"}}